Mason's Amazing Algos

(A)
Goal: Identifying poor decorator patterns
for class in package
    methods = class.methods()
    for m in methods
        if m.isDecorator
            if m.parameter.isNotUsed() (or some other way to see if a decorator is "bad")
                return false

(B)
Goal: Identifying invalid equals or hashcode override

for class in package
    methods = class.methods
    for m in methods
        if m.override and m.equals or m.hashcode
            if !m.contains(m.equals and m.hashcode)
                return false
            if both m.equals xor m.hashcode override
                return false

(C)
Goal: Identifying poor Global Variable placement/style

for class in package
    variables = class.variables
    for v in variables
        if v.isGlobal
            if v.InMethod()
                 if v.isNotCaps()
                    return false
              return false
     return true

(4)
Goal: Identify instances of missing implementations of abstract methods

for class in package
    if class extends
        necessary_methods = getAbstractMethods(class.extends)
        for method in necessary_methods
            if !class.methods.contains(method)
                return false
         return true